parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect for Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can lead to delays in fixing safety-critical issues, potentially putting riders at risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available
manufacturer unable to provide a date for parts availability
delays in scheduling recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body cams can cause the engine to run poorly, resulting in a loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine runs poorly
lacks power
and may stall when accelerating from a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump quick disconnect can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, engine stall, or loss of power, potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel leak at the fuel pump quick disconnect
fuel leak at the fuel pump neck
leak occurs only when the ignition is turned on and the fuel pump is pressurizing the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission flange can cause fluid leaks, leading to premature wear on transmission components, and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or become difficult to shift, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fluid leaks from the transmission
transmission flange is damaged or corroded
transmission fluid level is low
vehicle stalls or hesitates to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling issue in first gear can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls when stopped and in first gear
vehicle can be restarted immediately
stalling occurs frequently (e.g.
once a month).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering head bearing can cause the handlebars to loosen, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The handlebars feel loose or unsecured
the motorcycle is difficult to steer
the motorcycle wanders or drifts while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Final Drive Failure on BMW R1200RT Motorcycle
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive can cause the rear wheel to lose power, leading to loss of control, accidents, or rendering the rear brake useless, which can result in serious safety risks.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the rear wheel seal
oil saturation of the rear brake
rear wheel/final drive seal leakage
loss of power to the rear wheel
rear brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Wheel Crown Gear Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel crown gear bearing can cause the final drive to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, or rendering the rear brake useless, which can result in serious safety risks.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the rear wheel seal
oil saturation of the rear brake
rear wheel/final drive seal leakage
loss of power to the rear wheel
rear brake failure.
